OL,3,CHundreds of motorists caught drink-
OL,4,Cdriving four times or more
OL,6,FThat was 11% more than the previous
OL,7,Fyear, but 16% below 274,000 in 2019,
OL,8,Fbefore the coronavirus pandemic.
OL,10,FDepartment for Transport (DfT) figures
OL,11,Fshow an estimated 300 people were
OL,12,Fkilled in crashes on Britain's roads
OL,13,Finvolving at least one driver over the
OL,14,Flegal alcohol limit in 2022.
OL,16,FThat was up from 260 the previous year
OL,17,Fand was the highest total since 2009
OL,18,Fwhen 380 were recorded.
